cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about weakly and semi-supervised semantic segmentation, which is a task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach that utilizes dilated convolution, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning models. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves classification and segmentation, which are tasks related to natural language processing, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves image processing, which is a task related to multimedia, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
